<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="480" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[112,754,189,406]" pageId="1" pageNumber="480">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[113,243,189,213]" pageId="1" pageNumber="480">Comments.</emphasis>
It is a large genus with 37 valid species names (WSC, 2020). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1885" box="[275,365,222,245]" class="Arachnida" family="Lycosidae" genus="Hippasa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="480" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[275,365,222,245]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="480">Hippasa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is restricted to the Old World and known from Africa to 
<collectingCountry box="[361,424,254,277]" name="Japan" pageId="1" pageNumber="480">Japan</collectingCountry>
, north to 
<collectingCountry box="[531,638,253,277]" name="Tajikistan" pageId="1" pageNumber="480">Tajikistan</collectingCountry>
and south to 
<collectingCountry box="[143,280,285,309]" name="South Africa" pageId="1" pageNumber="480">South Africa</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[333,441,285,309]" name="Singapore" pageId="1" pageNumber="480">Singapore</collectingCountry>
(WSC, 2020). It is relatively well studied due to series of recent publications dealing with African and Asian species (
<bibRefCitation author="Alderweireldt M &amp; Jocque R" box="[413,747,349,373]" pageId="1" pageNumber="480" pagination="45 - 68" refId="ref4544" refString="Alderweireldt M &amp; Jocque R (2005) A taxonomic review of the Afrotropical representatives of the genus Hippasa (Araneae, Lycosidae). Journal of Afrotropical Zoology, 2: 45 - 68." type="journal article" year="2005">Alderweireldt &amp; Jocqu√©, 2005</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Wang LY &amp; Li ZX &amp; Zhou KX &amp; Zhang ZS" box="[115,315,381,406]" pageId="1" pageNumber="480" pagination="231 - 244" refId="ref5230" refString="Wang LY, Li ZX, Zhou KX &amp; Zhang ZS (2015) Redescription of three Hippasa species from China (Araneae: Lycosidae), with a proposed species group-division and diagnosis. Zootaxa, 3974 (2): 231 - 244." type="journal article" year="2015">Wang et al., 2015</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
